$ Bitcoin address

A Bitcoin address is a hash of a public key. Each Bitcoin address has its own unique private key.

A Bitcoin address is a base58 encoded string that contains
  • The address's version number
  • The hash
  • A checksum to detect errors


Bitcoin addresses are calculated from a public key: `RIPEMD-160(SHA-256(public-key))`.

A → development/Crypto-Currencies/Bitcoin/transactions[transaction] moves → development/Crypto-Currencies/Bitcoin/coin[Bitcoins] from one address to another.
-
So, at any given time, all then existing → development/Crypto-Currencies/Bitcoin/coin[bitcoins] are associated with a bitcoin address.

? A bitcoin address is represented in Base58 (for Segwit, in Bech32).

